txt.en: 'Ha, I believe I understand....'
'Ah... I believe I understand.'
'Limfind, where is Noriel?'
'I am here.'
'Such strange sorcery that hides this keep from the eyes of my people....'
'You have leave to speak, Wynmar, but then you must go.'
'Perhaps it is the magic of the Dwimordene that makes Noriel so fair, and her sword-skill so sharp!'
TBD!!!
'Fair lady, I wish to apologize for my people's invasion of your land.'
'Please come, [placeholder]; I must see her one last time before I abide her wish and leave this forest.'
'But... truth be told, that is not why I asked to be brought here.'
'How did she bewitch me so?'
'Ever since we met, I have yearned to meet you again.'
'Hold, trespasser!'
'I -- I cannot stop thinking about you.'
'I mean no harm!'
'Trespassers are not welcome in Thinglad. You have already been warned once, Wynmar of Stangard.'
'[placeholder], surely you had a reason for showing this outsider to our keep....'
'What motivated this unexpected visit?'
'Horse-rider, please --'
'I am called Wynmar.'
'Say no more, lady. You speak true.'
'Wynmar, Horse-rider, Trespasser, whatever you are called....'
'I... will abide your wish. The Men of Stangard will trouble your woods no more.'
'...I thank you for your help earlier, but you must leave immediately.'
'Wait! I think I am in love with you!'
'I do not know what to do, Noriel.'
'It is strange, I know, but no woman has ever struck my heart so!'
'This is foolish! Your people are the enemies of mine. Dwimordene you call us....'
'I do not know what madness has possessed you, but I do not wish to be involved.'
'Now, you must leave this place, Wynmar of Stangard.'
